----- Algorithm for Stack Operations -----

Step-1: Start the program
Step-2: Initialize:
       -> Stack array of size n
       -> top = -1
Step-3: Display the menu:
	      1. Push
	      2. Pop
	      3. Display
	      4. Exit
Step-4: Repeat until the user chooses to exit:
	    -> Read user's choice (opt)
	    -> If user chooses 1 (Push Operation):
			    => Check Overflow condition, top == n-1
			    => If not, increment top and insert value
	    -> If user chooses 2 (Pop Operation): 
			    => Check Underflow condition, top == -1
			    => If not, delete the top element and decrement top
	    -> If user chooses 3 (Display Operation):
			    => Check if the Stack is empty, top == -1
			    => If not, traverse the stack from top to 0 and display all elements.
	    -> If user chooses 4 (Exit):
			    => Display the exit message.
	    -> Otherwise:
			    => Display "Invalid choice"
Step-5: Stop the program			
